6. Bg4
7. Qd2{ Sidestepping the pin and thereby threatening  Ne5 . }
7. Bxf3
8. gxf3
8. Nbd7
9. e4{ We'll return to this position in  Chapter 3B.  White will likely castle long and aim to use both bishops to create some pressure, such as with  Bh3  and  Bh6 , although  Be3  may be better if Black delays castling, followed by expansion with  e4 - e5  and  f3 - f4 . }
