8. e4( { Aaron Summerscale's old suggestion makes a lot of sense to us, even if it remains in need of an over-the-board test, which is testament to how rare this position is. With Black having a knight on the rim, White expands in the centre. Of course, }8.O-O { is possible if you prefer, but do please avoid }8.Ne5? f6 { . } )
8. dxe4
9. Nxe4( { White has slightly the more pleasant game here. He would quite like to continue in aggressive fashion with  Qd2  and  O-O-O , and  Ng3  may also be a useful move - particularly }9...Bf5 10.Ng3! { , looking to clear the  h -file for action there. } )
