12. g4( { Played anyhow and this improves over the }12.dxc5 { of Chatalbashev-Djuric, Antalya 2002. White simply ignores Black's queenside pawn-storm, rightly trusting in the superiority of his own on the kingside. }12...b4 13.Na4 { would now head for  c5  and break up Black's pawns with some effect, so Black might try to counter on the other flank: } )
