11. e6( { After }11...c5 { , we'd be very tempted to go }12.hxg6 { , and if }12...fxg6 13.Bd3 { , but the following attacking set-up is also an instructive one:      }12.Qd2!? e6 13.hxg6 fxg6 14.Bg4! { A fine post for the bishop, pressing on  e6  while clearing the second rank. White will secure  e5  with  f2 - f4 , castle long and just has a fine attacking set-up. }14...Re8 15.f4 Qd7 16.O-O-O Nc6? 17.Ne4! { Whoops! The pin on the  d -pawn and imminent arrival of the knight on  f6  already forced resignation in Hebden-Likavsky, Cappelle-la-Grande 1992. } )
