13. Nxe5
14. dxe5
14. Nxg4
15. Nxd5{ This looks rather problematic for Black due to the pressure against  e7  and threat of  Nf6 +, but there is a defence, albeit not an obvious one to have spotted in advance: }
15. Qe8
16. Rhd3{ The position is quite unclear, but at least White is nicely centralised and ready to improve his pieces with  Bg3  and  f2 - f3 , while the knight can jump back to  c3  if attacked, looking then to take up a dream post on  e4 . }
