12. f3( { White calmly keeps the black knight out of  e4 . Alternatively, }12.h5?! Nxh5 13.Rxh5!? gxh5 14.Qxh5 Qd6 { doesn't seem especially convincing here and   }12.Rh3 Qb6! 13.Nxc6 Rxc6 14.Qxe7 Re8 { has been shown to offer Black decent enough counterplay. } )( { White can consider }12.g4!? { , though. With the centre secure after }12.f3 { , White would be quite happy to see }12...Nxe5?! 13.dxe5 { and is likely to meet anything slow with }13.g4 { or perhaps first }13.Kb1 { . } )
12. e6
