10. Nc6( { Good defence, countering against  d4 . Perhaps surprisingly, matters aren't so clear after }11.Qxd5 e6! { and   }11.Nxc6 bxc6 12.Qxc6 Bxd4 { should also give Black enough counterplay. } )
11. O-O-O{ One good move is countered with another. White overprotects  d4 , thereby renewing the threat against  b7  and  d5 . }
11. Nxe5
12. fxe5{ White can scarcely object to having his pawns undoubled after this engine suggestion for Black. }
12. e6
13. f4{ Cutting out ... Qg5 +, as well as strengthening White's wall of pawns to hinder Black's unopposed bishop. Now  Qxb7  followed by  Na4 - c5  is still a possibility and White may also yet obtain some pressure on the kingside with  g2 - g4  followed by  h4 - h5  or even a timely  f4 - f5 . }
