17. e6
18. Rd3( { There's no need to showboat with }18.Qxg7+!? Kxg7 19.Bg5 { here, not least when matters aren't totally clear after }19...f5! { . }{ Instead, White secures a safe spot for the king on  d2  and has the slow-motion but strong plan of  Rh3 ,  Rf3  and  Bg5 , exploiting Black's hamstrung bishop. } )
18. Qxa2
19. Kd2
19. Qa3
20. Rh3( { Black is unable to escape without jettisoning his bishop and the engines are long out of good suggestions for the defence. Blatny-Peek, Groningen 1990, concluded: }20...a5 21.Rf3 Rd7 22.Bg5 a4 23.Bf6! Bxf6 24.exf6 Ke8 25.Qh8+ Qf8 26.Rh3 { 1-0 Black is completely undone on the back rank. Slow but devastating play from the Barry expert. } )
