9. h4{ Our favourite advance and with Black solid but slightly slow on counterplay, it may not come as a surprise that White has scored pretty well from this position in practice. }
9. b5{ Black attempts to drive the knight away from  c3  then invade with ... Ne4 . }
10. f3{ Keeping Black out of  e4  and thereby renewing the threat to advance and quickly with  g2 - g4  and  h4 - h5 . }
