16. Rf5
17. f4{ With Black's bishop locked out of play, White was clearly better in Oliwa-Chojnacki, Polish Team Championship 2009. White can decide when to attempt a breakthrough on the kingside, not least  h4 - h5 , and is likely to first improve the pieces with  Qd3  and  Ne2 - d4 , bringing the knight to an ideal central location. }
