11. Bh2( { Preserving an important bishop, although it should be said that some experienced Barry players, including Ian Rogers, have been happy enough to swap it for a powerful pawn roller here with }11.g4!? Nxf4 12.exf4 { . } )( { After the calm bishop retreat, we examined the position after }11...f5 12.f3 { via the   }9...Nh5 10.Bh2 f5 11.O-O-O c6 12.f3 { move order  here.  The engines suggest one other idea for Black: } )
11. Bxe5
12. dxe5
12. b5
13. Qe1{ A decent square for the queen and alternative to  d2 . White frees  e2  for the knight and we quite like his chances, with the clear and strong plan of  f2 - f4 ,  g2 - g4 ,  h4 - h5  and  Qh4 . }
