8. Qxe2{ There are no prizes for guessing that an  h2 - h4 - h5  advance is now high on White's radar. There's another possibility here, too, thanks to the queen already being on  e2 : some  Qb5 , generating potentially awkward pressure against  b7  and  d5 . That helps to explain why in practice Black normally prevents the queen raid at this point. }
