12. Kxg7
13. h5{ This simply leaves White with a free hand on the kingside.  Qd2  and/or  e3 - e4  may follow. }
13. Nf6
14. g4{ Switching plans now that Black has begun to challenge for control of  e4  and because a timely  g4 - g5  may prove useful. }
14. Qd6
15. f3( { This isn't the only good move here and }15.f4 { was also quite strong in Wirthensohn-Ekstroem, Zurich 1994, but the text move seems simpler to play. There's no need to rush as White with Black not exactly up to much, but at some point White will roll forwards in the centre with  e3 - e4 , likely prefaced by  Qd2  and maybe even  Kb1 . } )
