10. Qd8
11. O-O{ This was surely going to be needed at some point, so it might as well be played now. White has a lead in development and some extra space, but Black is, of course, still quite solid. As  Ne5  would now only really help Black free his position, White is more likely to look towards  Nc5  ideas or even the  c3 - c4  break. Indeed, one decent plan would be  Rc1 ,  Nc5  and  c3 - c4 . }
11. Ne4
12. Rc1( { We slightly prefer this consistent move to the }12.Qb3 { of Akash Pc-Tukhaev, Mumbai 2017. } )( { Now }12...-- 13.c4 { may be possible, and if }13...dxc4 14.Bxc4 b5? 15.Bd3 { . } )
