10. Ne4( 10...Ne8?! 11.Bxg7 Kxg7 { and now }12.e4 { was played in Yusupov-Zinchenko, Warsaw }{ (rapid) }{ 2007. Against Black's slightly passive approach, }12.g4! { seems stronger, and now White should certainly not fear a race scenario. }12...b5!? 13.f3 a5 14.O-O-O! { Fearless play, but everything is now well coordinated and White all set to break with  e3 - e4 , which should leave him with a pleasant advantage. Observe too how it's still far from easy for Black to get anywhere on the queenside, }14...b4 { merely driving the knight towards  c5  after }15.Na4 { and with }14...a4 15.a3! { placing a certain brake on the black pawns. } )
