11. f5
12. Qd2( { We prefer this calm choice to the radical }12.f4 { of Van de Mortel-Ty.Hughes, Chicago 2006. } )
12. Nf6
13. O-O-O{ Now  hxg6  followed by  f2 - f3  and  g2 - g4  may occur and there's actually no need to rush with  f2 - f3  before castling as an invasion on  e4  by Black will only help White. }
13. Ne4
14. Nxe4
14. fxe4
15. f4( { Black only faces a choice of evils: to take en passant and come under heavy pressure down the  g -file too after }15...exf3 16.gxf3 { or to see White increasing the pressure with  Qe1  followed by  Qg3  or  Qh4 . } )
