14. Na4{ Black has the big centre, but is it a strength or potential target? White would quite like to invade on  b6  or cause problems with  Nbc5  and may also ask some pertinent questions with  Bh4  or just the  c2 - c4  break. The engines think that Black should be OK, but White's position looks slightly the more pleasant and easier to play to us. Finally, do note that  a5  isn't really hanging: }
14. Nxa5
15. Nxa5
15. Qxa5
16. Bxe5{ Activating the bishop while isolated Black's  d -pawn.  Bd4  and  Nb6  may even follow with a pretty pleasant advantage for White. }
