9. a5
10. Nb1{ A perhaps unexpected, but also notable and fairly strong manoeuvre exploiting our control of  e5  and Black's lack of counterplay to improve the knight. Now White may just obtain a pleasant version of a London System after  Nbd2  and  c2 - c3 , and it may also be possible to get in  c2 - c4 , depending on how Black responds. }
10. Ne6
