7. Be2
7. Bg7
8. Ne5{ Consistent, and now  h4 - h5  is very much an idea, as is  g2 - g4 . }( { Black may even be concerned by the prospect of }8...h5 9.f3 { , but his other method of ruling out  h4 - h5 - h6  isn't completely advisable: } )
8. Qb6{ Countering in critical fashion against  b2 , a pawn which White actually doesn't have to defend. }
9. Nxd7
9. Nxd7
10. g4{ Forcing the pace and a nice idea from Okhotnik. }
10. Qxb2
11. Nxd5{ The star follow-up as White plays to acquire the bishop pair. }
11. Bxc2
12. Qc1{ Forcing the queens off. }
12. Qxc1+
