3. d5
4. Bf4( { Having examined the main lines of the Barry, and before we turn our attention to the modern trend for }4...Bg7 5.Nb5 { , there are a few sidelines for Black we should consider. } )
4. Bg7( { Black's main alternatives occur after this, although on the odd occasion he does prefer something other than this or }4...c6 { here. } )
5. e3( { Alternatives to }5...O-O { and, to a much lesser extent }5...c6 { , are rare, but here we should devote a section to two sidelines.  4A) }5...Nh5 { will be examined  here.   4B) }5...Bg4 { will be examined  here.   On the odd occasion, you may also get to face something even rarer. } )
5. a6
6. Be2( { Standard, straightforward development and now play is likely to go }6...O-O { when we saw }7.Ne5 { at the start of  Chapter One  via a   }5...O-O 6.Be2 a6 7.Ne5 { move order. In  any case, with all the minor pieces developed White is set to go  Ne5  and ideally  h2 - h4 . } )
6. c5
7. dxc5{ Our standard recipe: when Black goes in for an early ... c5 , we swipe the pawn. }
7. Qa5
8. O-O{ Not our standard approach as White moves quickly to attack  d5  and obtain some queenside pressure, aiming to prove ... a6  a weakening advance. }( { If you still want to play by analogy with  Chapter 2A  then by all means prefer }8.Nd2 Qxc5 9.Nb3 Qc6 10.Bf3 { . } )
8. Qxc5
9. Na4{ A key follow-up. There is a potential hole on  b6 , but White's immediate aim is to activate all his forces with  c2 - c4 . }
9. Qa5
10. c4( { Now  Rc1  or  c4-c5  may follow and there's actually an even bigger positional threat: }10...-- 11.b4! { followed by }11...Qd8 12.c5 { or }11...Qxb4? 12.Rb1 { and  Nb6 . } )
10. Bd7
11. Nc3{ The knight leaps back, renewing the pressure against  d5 . }
11. dxc4
12. Ne5{ White will regain the pawn with a small but pleasant edge and Catalan-type pressure after  Nxc4 ,  Qb3  and maybe also  Bf3 . And, yes, Black would be ill advised to try and hang on to the pawn: }
12. b5
13. Bf3
13. Ra7
14. Nxc4( { White is winning material, whether after }14...bxc4 15.Bxb8 { (the rook is trapped) or   }14...Qd8 15.Qd4 { . } )
