8. c5
9. c3{ This is always a well-timed response to ... c5 , shoring up  d4  and ensuring that ... Qb6  can always be met by  Qb3 . }
9. b6
10. Nb5{ A fourth move with the knight and one which leaves White with a pleasant edge. The knight will be supported by  a2 - a4  and meanwhile, its counterpart is rather tied to  a6  by the need to cover  c7 . }
