8. Bd7( { Challenging for control of  b5  must be fairly critical. If }8...Bf5 9.Be2 { Once again, both  O-O  and  a2 - a4  will improve White's position and emphasise who is in control. }9...Qd7 10.a4 Rfd8 11.O-O h6 12.Bh2!? { .  This prophylaxis avoided any issues with ... g5  and left White clearly for choice in Sjugirov-Ozdemir, Titled Tuesday Blitz 2020.  Ne5  is very much on the agenda, after which White may have ideas of a timely  dxc5  or simply kingside expansion, not least with  f2 - f4  and  g2 - g4 . } )
