11. a4{ Even here White looks to be doing pretty well, since he will castle kingside, centralise the rooks and can also flick in a timely  Bh6 . }( { Now }11...Bxe5? 12.Bb4 { would win material and there's another trap Black must avoid: } )
11. a6
12. O-O{ A powerful sacrifice. }
12. axb5
13. Bb4( { Pinning Black's queen unless they wants to be mated on  e7 . If we take stock after the forced continuation }13...g5 14.Qxg5 Qxb4 15.Qxg7 Rf8 16.Ng5 { , we find White with a monstrous initiative and set to regain our material with significant interest after  Nxh7 . } )
