13. h3{ Another useful move with tempo. }
13. Bxf3
14. Bxf3{ And yet another. }
14. Bxh6
15. Qxh6
15. Ng7
16. h4{ Black had brought the knight back to safety on  g7 , but was still worse in Jumabayev-J.Van Foreest, Titled Tuesday Blitz 2020. There, White was all set to strengthen his grip on the kingside with  g2 - g4  and  Ne2 - g3 , probably then followed by dropping the queen back and looking to go  h4 - h5  when ... g5  would be an extremely ugly response for Black. }
